        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to Francis’s attending the hospital and by the subject matter of the letter (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Francis began studying medicine at St George’s Hospital, London in 1871 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5933.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi></ref>). CD was studying the movement of facial and neck muscles, including the platysma myoides, for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, which was published in 1872.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 300–1, CD described the contraction of the platysma in frightened patients, and cited <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3579.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Ogle</ref> as his informant.</note>
        </div>        
            
